Detailed Description

cvmx_usbc::_daint

Device All Endpoints Interrupt Register (DAINT)

When a significant event occurs on an endpoint, a Device All Endpoints Interrupt register interrupts the application using the Device OUT Endpoints Interrupt bit or Device IN Endpoints Interrupt bit of the Core Interrupt register (GINTSTS.OEPInt or GINTSTS.IEPInt, respectively). There is one interrupt bit per endpoint, up to a maximum of 16 bits for OUT endpoints and 16 bits for IN endpoints. For a bidirectional endpoint, the corresponding IN and OUT interrupt bits are used. Bits in this register are set and cleared when the application sets and clears bits in the corresponding Device Endpoint-n Interrupt register (DIEPINTn/DOEPINTn).
